To collect the sugar cane, you can use a piston and an observer. Later you can make an §6Auto-Breaker§r from §bActually Additions§r, which works even better and doesn't spill sugar cane everywhere.

For now, a §3Vacuum Chest§r should help keep the floor clean, and causes less lag than Hoppers. A §aVoid Upgrade§r in a §6Storage Drawer§r will automatically delete any items that overflow the drawer's capacity, so it's a good way to ensure you don't crash your server from accumulating a massive sugar cane pile before safer block breakers are available to you.

There's a great deal of interesting content within §bExtra Utilities 2§r, and although most of it is not required for progression, you should still look through what it offers and build what interests you.

In particular, the §aAngel Ring§r bauble offers creative flight, and although some of the RF generators are not particularly good, others are quite competitive with the Dynamos. And of course, you can aim for the all powerful §aRainbow Generator§r as you work towards endgame. All that and much more await, so explore away!

If you've tried to insert or remove a lot of items quickly, you might notice your ME network
§eflickers offline§r briefly. This is because digitizing and re-materializing items requires energy!

Your network doesn't naturally store very much energy and the §6Energy Acceptor§r only intermittently refills the network's power. To keep things stable, you will need to add some energy storage in your network using §6Energy Cells§r.

Just place one anywhere in your network and it will fill up with AE energy received from the Energy Acceptor. Now, you should have enough energy in your network to prevent these power losses. Feel free to add more energy cells, or upgrade to §6Dense Energy Cells§r, if you continue to experience problems.

If you've opted to enable channels in your AE2 configs, you will innately have some energy storage from the §3ME Controller§r, but we assume you know what you're doing at that point. §eAE2 Channels mechanics are outside the scope of the quest book, and this is the only time it will be mentioned.

Endervoirs are blocks that generate water much faster than basic NuclearCraft infinite water sources.

Endervoirs are multiblocks formed by at least three Endervoir blocks. You can right-click a block with a wrench to make it output into adjacent machines.

The maximum transfer rate of an Endervoir is one bucket per second.

With your Rocket built, fuel loaded, and destination set, it's time for the prelaunch checklist.

- §eMake sure you're wearing your Space Suit§r (all four pieces) and that it has a full tank of Oxygen. If you plan to stay on the Moon a while, maybe bring a gas charging pad and Ender Tank (being filled with Oxygen) with you.

Teleportation:

- If you decided to go with §aDislocators§r, make sure you take two with you: one bound to the Overworld, the other ready to bind to the Moon. Also bring along a Pedestal to put the Overworld one on the Moon surface.

- If you decided to go with §aTelepads§r, make sure you've constructed a Telepad in the Overworld and that you're carrying coordinates that lead to it. Make sure to bring your Coordinate Selector, blank Paper, and materials for the second Telepad setup. Bring Dew of the Void and RF power (like a §6Solar Panel§r and a §6Capacitor Bank§r).

In either case, as soon as you land you will need to prepare the other half of the teleportation route, and chunkload it.

When you're sure you're prepared, sit in your rocket and press §eSpace§r.

Liftoff!

There's a great deal of interesting content within §bActually Additions§r, and although most of it is not strictly required for progression, you should still look through what it offers and build what interests you.

In particular, the §aDrill§r with all the upgrades is a fantastically powerful mining tool, and the §3Vertical Digger§r is a machine which can be placed to automate mining an entire vein for you.

§3Phantomfaces§r, §3Auto Placers/Breakers§r, §3Lava Factories§r, and much more can be utilized at your discretion to supplement and refine your automation techniques.

§6Barium§r is an element found in §6Barite§r, which may be found as §6Barite Ore§r, inside §6Quartz§r veins.

Barite can also be extracted from other Quartz ores via ore processing.
Melting §6Mana Dust§r in a §3Fluid Extractor§r produces §9Primal Mana§r, which is needed for smelting various alloys from §bThermal Expansion§r.

§6Transistors§r are semiconductors that can amplify or switch electrical signals and power. They're probably one of the most important inventions of the 20th century.

You're going to use them as a component for better circuits. This one is a bit pricey, requiring §6Aluminium Foil§r and §6Fine Silver Wire§r.

§bApplied Energistics§r uses §aPresses§r found in chests at the heart of meteors as templates for §3Inscribers§r to make §6inscribed circuits§r.

This compass will lead you to the nearest meteor impact. Use your favorite mining tools to smash through the §6Skystone§r shell and get to the juicy center where the §6Skystone Chest§r with the plate is found.

Please note that while they're often in a big crater, the meteors might be buried underground; when the compass is spinning wildly, you're right on top of one.

The Eighth Micro Miner.

The main source of §6Chaos Shards§r: as with Nether Stars and Withers, farming these in the needed amounts from Chaos Guardians would be absurd.

The other mission gives negligible amounts of §6Neutronium§r and some other moderately useful things, but you're better off making Neutronium in the §3Fusion Reactor Mark 3§r§r and the other items are otherwise craftable.

§6Chaos Shards§r are an endgame component for §bDraconic Evolution§r.

They are the base material for Chaotic Tier materials and come exclusively from Tier Eight Micro Miners.

Technically they also come from Chaos Guardians, but in the quantities you'll need these? That would be a silly prospect.

The Ninth Micro Miner.

Combines §bStellar Creation Data§r into the §dUniverse Creation Data§r, which is a crucial component for the Tier Ten Micro Miner mission.

The alternate mission brings a decent quantity of §6Neutronium§r, but you have to bootstrap it with some Neutronium from the §3Fusion Reactor Mark 3§r anyway. It might be easier to just make all your Neutronium in the reactor, but it's up to you.
Heavy plating used exclusively for the Tier Eight Micro Miner.

The most advanced substrate available, crafted and grown with bleeding-edge bioengineering technology.

§6Wetware Lifesupport Circuit Boards§r are the basis of §6Wetware§r circuits, the final theme that spans tiers six through nine.
§6Superconductor coils§r are the eighth coil material available, increasing your EBF's operating temperature to 9001K so it can process more advanced materials.

§6Awakened Draconium§r, §6Chaos Shards§r, and §6Stabilized Einsteinium§r can be used in a Draconic Tier fusion crafting setup to create a §6Draconic Reactor Core§r.

This is an important component in the Tier Nine and Tier Ten Micro Miners, as well as some Endgame items.

Heavy: avoid dropping it on your foot.

This special plating is used for two things-- Tier Two Micro Miners and the Space Station Assembler.

Heavy Plating for Micro Miners made from §6Tungsten Carbide§r.

You'll need an §3EV Compressor§r to make these.

This quest, and the ones that follow it, are §cNOT REQUIRED§r for progression.

Only do them if you want to be able to explore the various planets offered by Advanced Rocketry and potentially build bases there, or in space.

Refer to the various high quality tutorials on AR available on youtube for specifics.

The §3Warp Core§r is a multiblock structure that you can build on the space station. Use the Holo-Projector for a building guide.

While it's not required for the progression, you can spend some resources to travel to distant planets, either to explore them or just to change the background of your space station.

The Input Hatch must be filled with §6Dilithium§r.

§6Dilithium Crystals§r are used to power Warp Cores, and are also a key component in several Micro Miner missions.

They are made by crystallizing §6Dilithium Dust§r with §9Deuterium§r in an §3Autoclave§r.

The Fourth Micro Miner.

All of the Tier Four missions require §68 Quantum Flux§r and a stack of §6Petrotheum Dust§r.

This miner is the first convenient source of §6Osmium§r and §6Iridium§r, via a mission requiring §6Wither Realm Data§r.

A §6Composition Sensor§r instead directs the miner to obtain §6Dense Oilsands Ore§r, equivalent to 32 stacks of §6Oilsands Ore§r.

When equipped with a §6Gemstone Sensor§r:
§6* Dense Redstone Ore
* Dense Emerald Ore
* Dense Diamond Ore
* Dense Lapis Ore
* Dense Coal Ore§r

The Fifth Micro Miner.

The only source of §6Naquadah Dust§r.

When provided with §6Stabilized Uranium§r, brings:
§6* Uranium 238 Ore
* Molybdenite Ore
* Tennantite Ore
* Bastnasite Ore
* Sphalerite Ore
* Palladium Ore
* Beryllium Ore
* Monazite Ore
* Osmium Ore
* Enderpearl §mOre§r§6 Blocks
* Boron Dust§r

§6Iridium§r is an advanced material used for Micro Miner plating, §6ZPM Machine Hulls§r, and for alloying with §6Osmium§r into §6Osmiridium§r.

§6Iridium Ore§r is available renewably from the Tier Four and Tier Six micro miners.

It can also be reliably obtained from purifying §6Platinum§r or Osmium§r in a §3Chemical Bath§r, as well as from ore processing Osmium generally.

The Sixth Micro Miner.

The first decent source of §6Dragon Eggs§r and §6Stabilized Einsteinium§r.

Is also useful for:
§6* Uranium 238 Ore
* Iridium Ore
* Osmium Ore

An alloy of equal parts §6Tungsten§r and §6Carbon Dust§r.

§6Tungsten Carbide§r is a very dense, sturdy, and heat-resistant material useful for a variety of applications.

The Seventh Micro Miner.

The source of §6Dragon Hearts§r and the valuable §6Lair of The Chaos Guardian Data§r.

As a bonus, brings §6Dragon Eggs, Dragon's Breath, Ender Dragon Scales§r and a plenty of different precious metals and gems.
Heavy plating used exclusively for the Tier Seven Micro Miner.

§6Awakened Draconium§r is a powerful material used for crafting high-grade components, items, and machines from Draconic Evolution.

Five §6§6Draconium Blocks§r can be processed in a Wyvern Tier fusion crafting setup to create an equal output of five §6Awakened Draconium Blocks§r. At §e24 Billion RF per craft§r, you better have a handle on your power infrastructure.

Your first MV hull is as good of a place as any to consider yourself graduated from LV.

You might notice that these hulls can be made more cheaply in an §3Assembling Machine§r, but you don't have that weird fluid. Don't worry, you'll be able to make that soon.

§3Electrolyzers§r use electricity to separate items into their more basic components.

For example, you can break down Water into §9Hydrogen Gas§r and §9Oxygen Gas§r, or break down §6Clay Dust§r into §6Sodium Dust§r, §6Silicon Dust§r, §6Lithium Dust§r, and §6Aluminium Dust§r.

Having unlocked §6Signalum§r and §6Lumium§r, at long last you can now make §aSignalum Upgrade Kits§r!

Provides more augment slots to machines and dynamos.

Dynamos operate at §a500% of base power and fuel burn rate§r.

Portable Tanks hold §a800 buckets§r.

Machines operate at §a400% of base speed§r.
An advanced ingredient used for the §aUltimate Extended Crafting Table§r and other late-game recipes.

§6Indium§r is a rare material requiring specialized bulk ore processing to acquire. It is useful for making §6Indium Gallium Phosphide§r (InGaP).

If you were enterprising enough to discover and make §6Platinum Group Sludge Dust§r for early §6Osmium§r and §6Iridium§r, you'll be familiar with the general process.

You will need to purify (with a §3Washer§r or §3Chemical Bath§r) §6Galena§r and §6Sphalerite§r to get §6Crushed Purified§r dusts. These need to be placed together in a §3Chemical Reactor§r along with §9Sulfuric Acid§r, which will result in §9Indium Concentrate§r.

This in turn needs to be reacted with §6Aluminium§r in another Chemical Reactor, to create §6Tiny piles of Indium Dust§r and §9Lead-Zinc Solution§r. The latter can be electrolyzed into various useful materials, and the Indium piles can be combined into full dusts.

betterquesting:10.name:8: The Fourth And Final Tier Four Circuits
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
With your new §6Multi-Layer Fiber-Reinforced Epoxy Circuit Boards§r, §6QBit CPUs§r, and some standard components, you can make the final type of Tier Four Circuit: the §6Quantum Circuit§r.

As the best form of Tier Four circuit, these should be automated and stockpiled. The variant recipe requiring §6Advanced System-on-Chip§r won't be available until ZPM.

§6QBit CPUs§r are an advanced Circuit Wafer crucial for §6Quantum Circuits§r.

There are two methods of creating them:

The simpler recipe uses two §6Quantum Eyes§r and two ingots worth of molten §9Gallium Arsenide§r to enhance a §6NanoCPU Wafer§r. This recipe is slow and requires substantially more §9Radon§r per craft.

The other route instead uses §6Indium Gallium Phosphide§r and a tiny amount of Radon. This skips the slow-crafting Quantum Eyes, using far less Radon in the process, but requires the infrastructure in place for obtaining §6Indium§r.

The second route is overall better, and you will need Indium processing to complete the pack so might as well do it.

§6Arsenic§r can be obtained through the electrolysis of §6Cobaltite§r or §6Tennantite§r.

The latter comes renewably from a Tier Five Micro Miner mission, and Cobaltite can be found or purchased with §dOmnicoins§r.

§9Radon§r will be needed in large quantities.

For now, you'll need to obtain it from Tier Two Micro Miner missions, in the form of §6Radium Salt§r. Electrolyze it for Radon and §6Rock Salt§r.

Later it will be possible to make Radon using a §bGregTech§r §3Fusion Reactor§r.
Nothing new here, just use more standard circuit stuff and you can upgrade several §6Quantum Circuits§r into a §6Quantum Processor§r.

§6Power IC Wafer§r may be new if you skipped some of the battery quests, but it is now relevant. 

Using these wafers, some §6Chrome Plates§r, a §6Quantum Eye§r, and §6Signalum Wire§r, several §6Quantum Processors§r may be upgraded into a §6Quantum Processor Array§r.

Macerators are useful for grinding things down. The best application for one right now would be grinding down clay or terracotta into §6Clay Dust§f.

LV Macerators lack byproduct slots. MV Macerators get one byproduct slot, but unfortunately the §6Stone Dust§r byproduct is prioritized so in practice you get a bit less than advertised. HV Macerators and better have all three slots.

Macerator byproduct chances are doubled for each tier after MV. Here's the list of chances for ore byproducts for a quick reference:
§a§r• LV: §c0%
§r• MV: §a14%§c*
§r• HV: §a28%
§r• EV: §a56%
§r• IV and better: §a100%§r

The §6Reactor Stabilizer§r is a component needed for the Tier Nine and Tier Ten Micro Miners, as well as a component in a few Endgame recipes.

They are made in a Chaotic Tier fusion crafting setup, requiring a whopping §e56 Billion total RF each§r. You're gonna need some serious power generation and crafting infrastructure to make everything for these.

The first tier of §6capacitors§r. These (or stronger versions) are required to make §bEnderIO§r machines run. They're also used as components in a variety of recipes.

Higher tier capacitors will significantly increase the speed at which these machines operate, among other machine-specific properties.

Mixes two dusts to make a third.

For now, you'll be using it to make Glowstone Dust and Energetic Blend.

Glowstone Dust is made from Phosphor Dust and Gold Dust, or you could gather it from the Nether.

Energetic Blend is made from Glowstone Dust and Redstone Dust.
§6Dragon Hearts§r are needed for both §6Awoken Draconium§r and §6The Ultimate Material§r.
§6Luminessence§r is used in a number of things, but right now, it will be a component in your §aExtended Crafting Tables§r.
§9Phosphorus§r, §9Oxygen§r, and §9Water§r combine together into §9Phosphoric Acid§r.
You can combine various items with a §6Blank Data Model§r for a completed §6Data Model§r that you can run inside the §3Simulation Chamber§r.

"§6Dragon Eggs§r?" You might ask. Yep.

The final circuit theme, Wetware, will require a lot of them.

Tier Six Micro Miners can get some eggs (enough for this quest, as it happens), but Tier Seven miners are a better long-term solution for building up your supply, as they also give §6Dragon Hearts§r.

Later, you'll also get substantial quantities from Tier Eight Micro Miners, while you are accumulating §6Chaos Shards§r.

Man, that's a LOT of quests linked to this one.

§dOmnium§r, as the name suggests, is an incredible material composed of all elements and alloys you've encountered so far.

Fun fact: you'll need to make 487 motes. You've got all this automated, right?

Fluix is initially made via in-world crafting, by dropping §6Redstone Dust§r, §6Nether Quartz§r, and a §6Charged Certus Quartz Crystal§r in the same block of §9Water§r. You'll see some sparks then the items will merge into a §6Fluix Crystal§r. Be sure to turn off any nearby item magnets/collectors or they might interrupt this crafting process.

The §3Energy Acceptor§r converts RF power into AE power that Applied Energistics uses, in a 2 RF to 1 AE ratio. This power will be transmitted through adjacent full-block ME Network devices, as well as along all connected §6ME Cables§r, §6ME Conduits§r, and §6Quartz Fiber§r. 

Quartz Fiber are §emicroparts§r you can put between an ME Cable and any ME Network block or another ME Cable. This will allow transmission of AE power but not data, which is useful for having data-isolated ME Networks all sharing the same power source.

With your §6Lumium§r-based machine hulls, Assembling Machine built, and §6Quantum Processor Mainframes§r squared away, you can finally get on the path to making a Ludicrous Voltage §3Assembling Machine§r.

This tier of Assembling Machine unlocks §6Crystal Circuits§r, as well as handling crafting recipes up to 32768 EU/t. It can also optionally overclock recipes up to 8192 EU/t for improved speed at the cost of relatively more power.

§6Vanadium-Gallium§r is an alloy made in the §3Electric Blast Furnace§r. It is a Ludicrous Voltage (LuV) cable material needed for certain recipes.

§6Vanadium§r is an element acquired by processing §6Vanadium Magnetite Ore§r.

The §3Assembly Line§r is a large multiblock structure that crafts complex materials, similar to an §3Assembling Machine§r. These will be crucial going forward for making a variety of components and machinery.

Make sure your power generation and circuit production are up to the challenge. It is useful to make at least two of these to avoid recipe conflicts and for different programmed circuits.

Notice that all numbers of required items are §emultiples of 12§r. This is to make an Assembly Line that's 12 units long, allowing for 11 inputs and one output. This is a large enough Assembly Line to make a §aFusion Reactor Controller Mk1§r, but you'll need to expand to more inputs for later projects.

§aFluid Input Hatches§r can replace any of the §6Steel Casings§r along the bottom outside except for the Casings touching the §aOutput Bus§r. For the most part, ULV ones work fine, but a few recipes will need an LV one.

The §aEnergy Input Hatches§r along the top can be replaced by Steel Casings: you only need the one Energy Input Hatch (although you can add more if you want).

The §aInput Buses§r along the bottom §emust be ULV tier§r, nothing else. Make sure to spin them all so the hole is on the bottom.

Time to get fusing!

The §3Fusion Reactor§r is a multiblock that uses enormous amounts of energy to fuse fluids into new elements. This one is less flexible than the previous GregTech multiblocks, as you can only put hatches where the preview shows.

The §bJEI§r preview shows §e§eall valid hatch locations§r, but you don't actually need that many fluid hatches. You can replace any of the hatch positions in the structure with §6LuV Machine Casings§r, as long as you have at least §atwo Fluid Input Hatches§r and §aone Fluid Output Hatch§r. It's possible to use input/output hatches in every valid location, if you prefer.

Because of this, the quest only asks for §a80 LuV Machine Casings§r. If you want to use the minimum number of fluid hatches, you'll need to craft an additional §a28 casings§r.

Each §aEnergy Input Hatch§r increases the reactor's power buffer. The "Energy to Start" value of a recipe is drained instantly when the reactor switches from the previous recipe it ran (or no previous recipe) to a different recipe. §aAll 16 Energy Input Hatches§r are required to be able to process all Mark 1 recipes.

If you can't provide sufficient starting power or continuous energy, §cthe craft might be voided§r. Make sure you have enough power to start up the reactor and to run the recipe to completion.

Fusion Reactors don't overclock, and they gate the next tier of materials, so you will eventually want to make more than one.

You'll need at least §6Naquadah Coil Blocks§r in your blast furnace to smelt §6Draconium§r, as well as a healthy supply of §9Cetane Diesel§r to reach the immense heat it takes to liquefy.

Draconium gets so hot that it requires the potent coolant §9Gelid Cryotheum§r to aid your §3Vacuum Freezer§r in turning it into usable ingots.

There are several ways to make Draconium: dust can be smelted into ingots, but you can also turn §6Ender Dragon Scales§r, which contain Draconium, directly into ingots. It uses a lot of Cetane Diesel, but is the most efficient way to craft Draconium.

You've been stockpiling diesel, right?

By baking an §6Exquisite Emerald§r and §6Emerald Plates§r with §9Helium§r in an §3Electric Blast Furnace§r, you can create an §6Engraved Crystal Chip§r.

This is a material needed for §6Crystal Circuits§r.

§6Crystal CPUs§r are the cores of §6Crystal Circuits§r.

You'll need an §3IV Precision Laser Engraver§r to craft this.
With some now-standard components you can upgrade a few §6Crystal Circuits§r into a §6Crystal Processor§r.

The culmination of so much effort.

§6Chaotic Cores§r are the ultimate tier of §bDraconic Evolution§r core, used for the most powerful and advanced items.

A gear forged from §6Empowered Restonia Crystal§r.

While you can empower gears directly, it makes much more sense to solidify them.

§bDraconic Evolution§r features §eFusion Crafting§r, which requires a §6Fusion Crafting Core§r and up to ten injectors of the appropriate tier.

You'll need eight §6Basic Fusion Crafting Injectors§r to upgrade any additional injectors you make to Wyvern Tier.

Yes, that means you should plan to make more than eight. If you really want to plan ahead, make thirty-four of these.

Obtaining §6Grains of Infinity§r will require you to mine all the way down to Bedrock level.

Use Flint and Steel to light a fire (or many fires) and then wait for it to go out. There's a 50% chance of Grains Of Infinity to appear for every fire that burns out on its own.

But who wants to do that forever? There will be better ways before too long, don't worry.

Mixing §6Titanium§r with §6Mana Dust§r creates §6Mana Infused Metal Dust§r. This can be smelted into ingots in an §3Electric Blast Furnace§r equipped with §6Kanthal Coils§r or better.

Mana Infused Metal is the basis of §bThermal Expansion§r device casings, and is used for many advanced §aAugments§r.

ASSEMBLE!

§6Mana Dust§r is an important material. It is needed for a variety of materials related to §bThermal Expansion§r.
This casing is the structure for §bThermal Expansion§r's devices, which are simpler machines.

§6Thermal Device Casings§r are upgradable to a §6Machine Frame§r with some §6Stainless Steel Plates§r.

These frames form the basis of §bThermal Expansion§r's more advanced machinery.
§6§6Redstone§r, a §6Snowball§r, and §6Blizz Powder§r creates §6Cryotheum Dust§r, a mixture imbued with potent elemental frost.
§6§6Redstone§r, §6Saltpeter§r, and §6Blitz Powder§r creates §6Aerotheum Dust§r, a mixture imbued with potent elemental air.
§6§6Redstone§r, §6Obsidian Dust§r, and §6Basalz Powder§r creates §6Petrotheum Dust§r, a mixture imbued with potent elemental earth.
§6§6Redstone§r, §6Sulfur§r, and §6Blaze Powder§r creates §6Pyrotheum Dust§r, a mixture imbued with potent elemental flame.
Bits of a §6Blaze Rod§r. Using a §3Macerator§r doubles your yield.
Bits of a §6Basalz Rod§r. Using a §3Macerator§r doubles your yield.
Bits of a §6Blitz Rod§r. Using a §3Macerator§r doubles your yield.
Bits of a §6Blizz Rod§r. Using a §3Macerator§r doubles your yield.

If you don't feel like searching for a Thermal Elemental, or can't because you're playing on Peaceful, you will need to make §eone§r batch of §9Elemental Reduction Fluid§r.

This will bootstrap being able to craft a §aThermal Elemental Model§r for DML, and you can get all of the rods from §6Thermal Elemental Pristine Matter§r going forward.

Praise the sun. \[T]/

This machine uses various tiers of §6Phyto-Gro§r and §9Water§r to grow plants.

It can be customized with various §aAugments§r.
§6Tungstensteel§r is the fourth coil material available, increasing your EBF's operating temperature to 4500K so it can process more advanced materials.

§6HSS-G§r is an alloy of §6Tungstensteel§r, §6Chrome§r, §6Molybdenum§r, and §6Vanadium§r.

This alloy is cooked in an §3Electric Blast Furnace§r and cooled in a §3Vacuum Freezer§r.
§6HSS-G§r is the fifth coil material available, increasing your EBF's operating temperature to 5400K so it can process more advanced materials.
Heavy plating made from §6Iridium§r for Tier Five and Tier Eight Micro Miners.
A heavy plating material required for the next two tiers of Micro Miners.
Heavy plating made from §6Enderium§r used for the Tier Six Micro Miner.
A complex plating material used exclusively for the Tier Nine Micro Miner.

There are two primary approaches to producing §9Epoxy§r: §9Bisphenol A§r (BPA) and §9Naphtha§r. Both approaches requre §9Epichlorohydrin§r, which itself has a few possible approaches.

Naphtha is the simplest approach, where it is mixed with §9Nitrogen Dioxide§r and Epichlorohydrin to yield Epoxy. This approach is easier but yields less Epoxy. You also forego making more diesel and getting distillation byproducts from Naphtha. If you have an extremely robust §9Oil§r drilling and petrochemistry infrastructure in place, this might be an acceptable choice.

BPA can be produced using petrochemistry distillation products, or via distilling §9Charcoal Byproducts§r from your §3Pyrolyse Oven§r into useful components. Alternatively, you can get §9Phenol§r from §6Coal§r pyrolysis. §9Fermented Biomass§r is also useful to distill as it provides many useful products. Epoxy made from BPA is more complex to set up initially, but also far more efficient.

The final decision is down to you make. Check out recipes in §bJEI§r.

You'll need large quantities of §6Canola§f (for §6Canola Oil§f in a §bCanola Press§f) and §6Sugarcane§f (for §6Ethanol§f).

Of course, other crops can work as well, if you want to mix things up.

A gear forged from §6Empowered Void Crystal§r.

While you can empower gears directly, it makes much more sense to solidify them.

A gear forged from §6Empowered Palis Crystal§r.

While you can empower gears directly, it makes much more sense to solidify them.

A gear forged from §6Empowered Emeradic Crystal§r.

While you can empower gears directly, it makes much more sense to solidify them.

An otherworldly material exclusive to Microverses, §6Naquadah§r is an important material in the late game.

Unlike most materials at this point, Naquadah can be smelted in a standard furnace.

It can be alloyed and enriched to various forms, and is the eventual source of §6Neutronium§r in a §3Mark Three Fusion Reactor§r.

§6Naquadah§r is the sixth coil material available, increasing your EBF's operating temperature to 7200K so it can process more advanced materials.

While it's also possible to make §6Naquadah Alloy Coils§r, you can skip them and go directly to §6Superconducting Coils§r.

With a §3Fusion Reactor§r, you can make Europium!

This element is needed for making things in §bDraconic Evolution§r§r, as well as the §6Fusion Reactor Computer Mark 2§r and §6Wetware Processor Arrays§r§r.

You make it by fusing molten §9§9Neodymium§r§r and §9Hydrogen§r.

§6Naquadah§r comes in a dust form and only from the Tier Five micro miner.

Get some, it's important. More on this later.

Just ignore the protesters outside your base.

Each craft in an §3LuV Chemical Reactor§r takes five minutes, so it's probably a good idea to have more than one machine running this recipe. At least you get a whole stack from a single egg.
§6Boron§r is currently obtainable by doing ore processing on §6Lepidolite Ore§r and §6Salt Ore§r (via §6Borax§r).

§6Basic Fusion Crafting Injectors§r can be upgraded to Wyvern Tier via fusion crafting.

Technically you only need six of these to start making the next tier of injectors, but some recipes will need more than that. Plan on making at least twenty-six of these.

§6Draconic Fusion Crafting Injectors§r are the penultimate tier of injectors for fusion crafting.

You'll need a fusion crafting setup with ten of these for the next tier of injector, and the next tier you'll also need ten injectors, so consider making 20 of these.

The highest tier of fusion crafting injectors. You will need at least ten of these to reach the §dCreative Portable Tank§r.

Each injector requires four ingots of §6Neutronium§r and four §6Chaos Shards§r, as well as two §6Crystal Matrix§r blocks.

Hope you've got those Tier Eight Micro Miners automated.

betterquesting:10.name:8: The Fourth And Final Tier Six Circuits
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
The final form of Tier Six circuits, and the final circuit theme.

Using your §6Wetware Lifesupport Circuit Boards§r, §6Naquadah Alloy wire§r, §6ASoCs§r, and §9Sterilized Growth Medium§r, you can craft (grow?) these circuits in a ZPM or better §3Assembling Machine§r.

These are fairly slow to craft and you're going to need considerable quantities, so make sure you have a good parallelized infrastructure for keeping these stocked.

betterquesting:10.name:8: The Third and Final Tier Seven Circuits
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§6Wetware Processors§r are made in an §3Assembly Line§r on ZPM power.

Among the usual kinds of parts, these require §6Frank'N'Zombies§r from a §3Soul Binder§r and §6Silicone Rubber Foils§r.

betterquesting:10.name:8: The Second And Final Tier Eight Circuits
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§6Wetware Processor Arrays§r are made in an §3Assembly Line§r at ZPM or better power.

You'll need §6Sentient Ender§r from §3Soul Binders§r and §6Europium§r from the §3Fusion Reactor§r to craft these.

betterquesting:10.name:8: The First And Only Tier Nine Circuit
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
The final circuit.

You'll need §6Tritanium§r for §6Tritanium Frames§r, which comes exclusively from the §3Fusion Reactor Mark 2§r or better reactor.

The §6Duranium§r needed to make Tritanium comes from the §3Fusion Reactor Mark 1§r or better.

Draconium is a complex material needed in vast quantities.

You'll likely have come by some dust while mining in the End, but you can also create it with §6Dragon's Breath§r and §6Manyullyn§r.

§6Draconic Cores§r are the first crafting step into §bDraconic Evolution§r.

These serve as the basis for crafting many items and can be upgraded into different tiers of cores via §eFusion Crafting§r.
HV Batteries function the same as LV and MV, only requiring more resources to craft.
With §6Titanium§r smelting automated, you can now build Machine Hulls for Extreme Voltage machines.

The Extreme Voltage tier §bGregTech§r battery. These are upgrades to the High Voltage tier battery, augmenting the §aEnergy Crystal§r with circuits and plates made of §6Lapis§r, §6Lazurite§r, or §6Sodalite§r.

Chances are by now you're not really using anything that needs GregTech batteries. You can safely ignore this quest until much later in the pack if you don't specifically need them.

An Insane Voltage tier §bGregTech§r battery.

You're unlikely to be using EU batteries so it's safe to skip this for now and do it later, though some of the infrastructure used for these batteries is also used for other things.

A Ludicrous Voltage tier §bGregTech§r battery.

You're unlikely to be using EU batteries so it's safe to skip this for now and do it later, though some of the infrastructure used for these batteries is also used for other things.

§3The Empowerer§r is a machine from §bActually Additions§r used to convert its special crystalline materials into empowered variants.

The Empowerer is placed in the center of a flat 7x7 region. The four §aDisplay Stands§r are placed with a two-block gap from the Empowerer, one in each cardinal direction.

Recipes require specific items to be placed on the Display Stands and the main item on the Empowerer itself. The items on the Display Stands are consumed and the central item is Empowered.

RF power needs to be fed into the Display Stands to infuse the center item with power. The Display Stands have a low per-side power transfer rate so it takes a while. Consider putting energy conduits on multiple sides of each display stand to speed it up a bit.

This thing's a bit of a pain. It's slow, takes up a large space, and it's cumbersome to automate. Don't worry, you'll get access to the §3Crafting Core§r after you get §6Draconium§r, which is vastly faster, more compact, and easier to automate. Even better, that's pretty much immediately craftable into the §3Combination Package Crafter§r, which can do the Empowerer recipes directly through §bPackagedAuto§r and §bAE2§r.

§6Wyvern Cores§r are the second tier of cores, used for intermediate crafting recipes.

Each Wyvern Core is made via fusion crafting and the setup needs eight §6Basic Fusion Crafting Injectors§r.

§6Steel Heavy Plating§r can be augmented with §6Tungsten Plates§r and §6Tough Alloy§r to make §6Basic Reactor Plating§r.

That's right-- it's time to get into §bNuclearCraft§r.

Tough Alloy is a couple steps to get to, but nothing too serious. Check §bJEI§r for more details.
Enhancing basic plating with §6YBCO§r and §6Hard Carbon alloy§r results in a better plating material for more advanced §bNuclearCraft§r blocks.

The full complexity of §bNuclearCraft§r is far too much for the scope of this quest guide, so §eyou're encouraged to watch a tutorial or read a guide online§r. For the purposes of this particular quest, you'll be building a cheap breeder reactor to make §6Plutonium§r.

First, set up your 54 §6Reactor Casings§r to encase a 3x3 cube shape of empty air. The Casings should only cover the faces of the interior cube, not the edges or corners. You should have exactly the right number of Casings to encase a 3x3 space.

Next, create a hole so you can get inside the cube. Place the §6Reactor Cells§r in all 8 corners. Then the §6Lapis Coolers§r will go between them: 4 on the top layer and 4 on the bottom layer. At this point, the top and botom layers should have eight blocks each with an empty middle, and the middle layer is fully empty. In the middle layer, place the 4 §6Graphite Blocks§r on the corners, and the 4 §6Glowstone Coolers§r on the sides (so they touch both Lapis Coolers). Now the cube should be full, except for an empty column in the middle. The reactor will now be complete when you reseal it up with the Casings you removed to access the interior.

Finally, place the §3Fission Reactor Controller§r along any edge or corner of the reactor. Opening the Reactor Controller GUI should let you know that the structure was properly formed; if not, go back and check what you did wrong.

The lever is placed on the reactor, as a redstone signal is required for it to start working. §cReactors can overheat and melt if the temperature exceeds its ability to cool.§r You can make a safety loop on the controller (instead of the lever) to automatically shut off the reactor when it starts getting hot using a §aRedstone Conduit§r, a §aRedstone Sensor Filter§r (on the input channel), and a §aRedstone NOT Filter§r (on the output channel). Make sure input and output are on the same channel color.

You don't need it just yet, but you can make it now.

This is a critical material for the Endgame.

If you don't want to mine Obsidian by hand, consider using a Fluid Solidifier to turn §cLava§r into §6Obsidian Blocks§r for you. The process is slow and energy intensive, though.

§3Fluid Solidifiers§r are useful for lots of other things too, of course. Look through the various molds to see what you can make with one.

The §aHang Glider§f is a great way to cross long distances, if you're so inclined.

If you don't want to go exploring for Cows, just buy a pair of "§6Spawn Cow§f" eggs and breed them. Seriously, spend your §dcoins§f!

A gear forged from §6Empowered Enori Crystal§r.

While you can empower gears directly, it makes much more sense to solidify them.
A catalyst forged from §dOmnium§r, §6Empowered Gears§r, various enhanced §6Nether Stars§r, and a core made of §6The Ultimate Material§r.

Are you ready to go infinite?

Reinforcing §6Heart of a Universe§r with §6Chaotic Cores§r, many §6Piles of Neutrons§r, and a bunch of §6Eternal Catalysts§r produces an §cInfinity Catalyst§r.

This material is the core of most creative-tier crafting recipes.

This ingot is the most advanced basic material.

With creative fluids and all the automation you hopefully set up for your first §c§cInfinity Catalyst§r, these ingots should be easy.

Well, not easy. But... Reasonable.

From here, you are going to be crafting a multitude of Creative-Tier items from various mods. In addition to being useful for their regular functionality, they are needed for the final goal: the §dCreative Vending Upgrade§r.

§bJEI§r is your friend: beyond noting a few more items, I will not be holding your hand anymore. I've taught you everything you need to know to beat the pack.

You can do it!
A helmet to surpass the ultimate, forged with the hearts of stars and the raw fury of the universe.
A chestplate to surpass the ultimate, forged with the hearts of stars and the raw fury of the universe.
Leggings to surpass the ultimate, forged with the hearts of stars and the raw fury of the universe.
Boots to surpass the ultimate, forged with the hearts of stars and the raw fury of the universe.
An ultimate helmet, forged from all manner of materials across dimensions and microverses.
An ultimate chestplate, forged from all manner of materials across dimensions and microverses.
An ultimate pair of boots, forged from all manner of materials across dimensions and microverses.
An ultimate pair of leggings, forged from all manner of materials across dimensions and microverses.

You win.

Congratulations.

I hope you enjoyed playing §5Omnifactory§r.

§oNow this is not the end. It is not even the beginning of the end. But it is, perhaps, the end of the beginning.§r

The §d§dCreative Portable Tank§r is a major milestone. Great work!

This tank is your first proper creative item, which can be set to a fluid and then provides an infinite quantity of that fluid. The first fluid you should do this with is §dMolten Creative Portable Tank§r, so you can make as many more tanks as you want! You get exactly enough from a §6Heart of a Universe§r to do this.

From there you can set up tanks with infinite quantities of every fluid you can think of.  §3Fluid Solidifiers§r can be used to make infinite of every element you can melt and solidify.

This is quite a game-changer as far as infrastructure goes. You'll find that many machines won't need to be used for their original purpose anymore. Some major base redesign is in order. Have you considered moving to space?

All that said, §ethe pack will still be challenging to complete§r. Infinite resources and power is nice, but it's not everything. There are plenty of materials you can't melt, and creative items will push your factory automation engineering skills to their limits.

Onward to the final challenge: the §dCreative Vending Upgrade§r!

A §aGrappling Hook§f is very useful in an urban enviroment.

There are lots of ways to upgrade and improve your Grappling Hook, so play around with it.

Open your inventory and look for the Baubles button, click it to reveal the additional bauble slots and put the Hook there.

The default key is §6C§r, however since quite a lot of mods occupy this hotkey you'll need to visit the controls menu to resolve the button conflicts.

No hoops to jump through here. Smelt §6Wood Logs§f to get §6Charcoal§f. It will serve you well as a fuel source until you locate a vein of §6Coal§f.

You might want to craft Charcoal into §6Tiny Charcoal§f pieces to save some fuel. One tiny piece is enough to smelt exactly one item. Just put charcoal into the crafting grid to make some!

A §aRubber Soft Hammer§f can be used to temporarily stop a machine from functioning. This is useful when you have two machines running and both are unable to keep going because of a lack of power... let one finish then turn the other one back on with a second hit from the hammer.
A component used for more advanced items related to §bExtended Crafting§r.
Again, combining a few Components will make a Catalyst.
This table allows you to craft 7x7 Extended Crafting Table recipes.
Combine several components into a catalyst.

Used for Ultimate tier §bExtended Crafting§r.

Don't worry if you can't make these for a while. You'll probably get to them around IV power.
This is the largest Extended Crafting Table, capable of handling 9x9 recipes.

Infuses things with Redstone Flux.

This is useful for charging RF-powered devices, but it also can also charge §6Rich Phyto-Gro§r into §6Fluxed Phyto-Gro§r, and charge §6Certus Quartz Crystals§r into §6Charged Certus Quartz Crystals§r.

ASSEMBLE... TOO!

Yeah you get to craft §6Nether Stars§r. Cool huh?

Over the course of the pack, Nether Stars are going to be needed in quantities that far exceed a reasonable player's ability to farm Withers. §eCraft them, don't bother trying to farm them.

Congratulations! You've reached the end of the circuit progression.

The only UHV circuit is the §6Wetware Mainframe§r, which is used for crafting high-tier micro miners among some endgame stuff.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Claim Your Chunks and Invite Teammates!
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
You might be wondering what chunkloading options there are in the pack.

Open your inventory and look at the top-left corner of the screen. Click the map-looking icon called §eClaimed Chunks§r.

§6Click a chunk§r to claim it as yours. This will prevent unwanted creeper explosions and other players from interacting with your base.

§6Shift-left click a claimed chunk§r to load it. This will ensure that the chunk is loaded at all times, even when you're not there. Alternatively, there are §achunk-loading wards§f from §bExtra Utilities§f.

§eIf you're playing on a server with custom settings, ask the server owner what methods are available§f.

To invite players to your §bFTB Utils§f party, look for a corresponding button in the same corner. Parties share claimed chunks with each other. You can configure permissions for your party's claimed chunks in the party settings menu.

Basic §aFlux Capacitors§r hold a whopping lot of energy - §a10 million RF§r - and are useful for keeping your §aRF-powered§r equipment and tools charged.

Put one into your newly crafted §3CEF§r to charge it. You can then put it in your inventory to charge your items with §aRF§r, or you can leave it in the CEF to act as a §a2.5 million EU§r battery!

Flux Capacitor is a §bBauble§r, open your inventory and look for the Baubles button, click it to reveal the additional bauble slots menu and put it into any slot you wish.

Finally you can charge up all those depleted §6Dark Boots§r and §6The Ender§r swords you've looted.

Very fluxy.

A reagent used in the majority of §6Micro Miner§r missions.

There are several ways to produce §6Quantum Flux§r. All are viable, so figure out which one works best for you.

A single-block solution to all your power needs.

This baby pushes out 2.14 GRF/t per side.

The §3Multi Smelter§r is an absolute smelting unit, and is most likely the best furnace added by a mod.

It's a 3x3x3 multiblock machine capable of §esmelting huge amounts of items per second§r. By upgrading its coils and power tier, it can become capable of smelting up to literal thousands of items per second.

Hover over different coil blocks: the higher the §elevel§r, the more items a Multi Smelter can smelt per operation: §e16 items per level§r. The most basic Multi Smelter essentially does 16 items in the same time as a furnace does one. With a set of level 4 coil blocks, that jumps to 64 items per operation.

This quest doesn't ask for coils, hatches or buses: feel free to choose whatever combination you want. You'll need §a8 coil blocks§r, §a1 input bus§r, §a1 output bus§r and at least §a1 energy hatch§r of any tier.

§3Large Plasma Turbines§r are a powerful late game method of generating power. One Large Plasma Turbine can produce nearly 41800 EU/t when using an §aLuV Rotor Holder§r and equipped with §a100% efficiency§r rotor.

One §3Mark 1 Fusion Reactor§r dedicated to producing §bOxygen Plasma§r can provide suffient fuel for continuously operating 16 Large Plasma Turbines, resulting in a combined production of roughly 670000 EU/t. Granted, this is a decent amount of infrastructure.

Don't rely on §bJEI§r too much when looking for the best plasma: fuels are displayed in a very misleading manner. A Large Plasma Turbine consumes up to nearly 16 buckets of plasma to run a cycle for the duration specified in JEI, and takes some time to spin up to full power.

Space exploration isn't mandatory in this pack, so if you don't feel like exploring space with §bAdvanced Rocketry§r, then you can centrifuge §9Hydrogen§r for §eDeuterium§r instead.

Just keep in mind that it's much less rewarding to skip this and you'll need lots of Hydrogen to compensate, although you won't need too much for the first §3Microverse Projector§r.

§3Anvils§f can be used to repair §bGregTech tools§f!

You might want to get yourself an anvil instead of breaking and crafting new tools every time. Anvils§f spawn abundantly in §bLost Cities§f buildings, so go and snatch one!

Put a damaged tool inside and put some material it's made of. For example, you'll need to put §6Wrought Iron Ingots§f to repair tools made of §6Wrought Iron§f.

GregTech adds a very versatile way of augmenting machines with §aMachine Covers§r. Covers are "upgrades" that you can put on any GregTech machine, chest, or drum to expand its functionality. To work with covers, you'll need to make yourself a §aScrewdriver§r to configure covers, and a §aCrowbar§r to remove covers without having to break the machine.

Here's a quick list of what covers there are in the game, and what they do:

- §a§lFilter§r: controls what items can enter or leave through a particular side, with 9 configurable slots and whitelist/blacklist modes. You can also put a filter into a §aConveyor§r or §aRobotic Arm§r to customize what items they will move. There's also a §9Fluid§r variant of the filter, which offers the same controls and can be placed in §aPumps§f.

- §a§lOre Dictionary Filter§r: a specialized filter that uses ore dictionary entries and supports "*" as a wildcard, e. g. "§6ingotHot*§r" will match all hot ingots, and "§6dustTiny*§r" will match all tiny piles.

- §a§lConveyor§r: transfers items to or from an adjacent inventory.

- §a§lRobotic Arm§r: is much like §aConveyor§r, but has two additional modes: §6Keep Exact§r, which keeps the exact amount of items in the inventory, and §6Supply Exact§r which transfers the exact amount of items per operation (useful for packaging tiny piles when used with §aOre Dictionary Filter§f!). This cover is very useful for crafting automation.

- §a§lPump§r: is much like a §aConveyor§f, but for fluids.

- §a§lShutter§r: prevents any interactions with a side.

- §a§lMachine Controller§r: enables or disables a machine and/or its covers depending on whether it is receiving a redstone signal. Useful when paired with §6ME level emitters§f to keep resources in stock.

All GregTech machines have one dedicated output side, which can be set by right-clicking a side with a §aGregTech Wrench§f. This is used for ejecting items into an adjacent inventory.

To enable auto-output, open the machine GUI and click one of the buttons in the bottom-left corner: §6orange§r is items and §9blue§r is fluids.

If you want to also be able to insert items into the output side, you'll have to right-click the output side with a §aGregTech Screwdriver§r.

These features can be used to chain machines together to make processing pipelines and facilitate crafting automation with §bApplied Energistics 2§f.

You can easily automate most §bGregTech§r machines with §aME Interfaces§r and processing §aPatterns§r early on by using the machines's auto-output feature.

Use a §aGregTech Wrench§r to relocate the output side of a machine where you want it to be, right-click it with a §aGregTech Screwdriver§r to permit input on the output face, then put an ME Interface on that side of the machine.

Right-click the machine and enable item auto-output (§6orange box§r in the bottom-left corner of the GUI).

Now, stuff the ME Interface with processing patterns. The next time you order an item, the ME Interface will push ingredients into the machine, and the machine will push outputs back into the Interface once they're ready, completing the craft. No need to use conduits or import buses!

This modpack has §aCrafting Calculators§r. It has a steep learning curve, but once you manage to learn how to use it, it's going to be your trusty companion in calculating recipe costs.

Craft yourself one and hit the book button in the top-left corner for a quick overview of how it works.

Now that you have §6Osmium§r and §6Iridium§r from the §6Tier Four Micro Miner§r, you can begin automating §bExtended Crafting§r recipes. While it is possible to use §6Automation Interfaces§r for this task, you have access to something §nvastly§r better§r: §bPackagedExCrafting§r.

To begin, you'll need to craft one of each extended §3Package Crafter§r listed on the right. Put an §3Unpackager§r on top of each one, and then a §3Packager§r on top of each Unpackager. These are all AE2 devices, so you'll need to connect them to an ME Network.

Next, right-click the §3Package Recipe Encoder§r, and you should see a button saying "Processing": this button cycles through recipe types, including the various Extended Crafting tables. You'll have to choose the appropriate table for the recipe you want to encode.

§6Holders§r must be encoded in pairs: one for the Packager, and one for the Unpackager. Select the appropriate table for the recipe, look up the recipe you want to encode, and press §6[+]§r in §bJEI§r to fill it in. Put two Holders in the top-left slot and press Save to encode the recipe to both of them. Finally, put each Holder into the respective machines.

If you've done everything correctly, you should see the item appear as craftable in a Terminal.

While it might seem that the crafting process is slow, §ePackagedAuto is excellent at parallelizing§r. You can surround an Unpackager with Crafters and it will use all of them. It's also possible to add more Unpackagers with Crafters to keep up with the Packager, as long as the Holders are all the same.

The §3Medium Microverse Projector§r is a more powerful projector required for sending Tier Four through Tier Six Micro Miners into microverses.

While some of the miners run on IV power, make a §6LuV Energy Input§r so you don't have to replace it later or accidentally try to run a Tier Six on IV power. Always check the voltage required on a recipe, as you will §close a miner§r if you can't supply enough power to complete the mission; ModMachines will continue to eat incoming power without making progress.

When building the multiblock, be sure to place the §6Quantum Compressors§r to face the same direction as the controller block (this is the usual reason for the structure not forming).

§bPackagedAuto§r is an addon for §bApplied Energistics 2§r. Its main purpose in §5Omnifactory§r is to allow you to automate extended crafting recipes.

Applied Energistics 2 stores recipes in §aPatterns§r, but they are limited to at most 9 stacks of items (a standard 3x3 crafting grid). PackagedAuto stores recipes in §aPackage Recipe Holders§r, which don't have this limitation. Additionally, each Holder can store up to §e20 different recipes§r. Holders must be encoded in the §3Package Recipe Encoder§r.

In the vast majority of situations you'll need two identically-encoded Holders, as the following machines work together.

The §3Packager§r is a machine that compresses ingredients for a specific recipe into a set of §6Recipe Packages§r. Each package in a set can hold up to 9 stacks of ingredient items. A simple recipe might consist of one package, but a complex recipe can have up to 9 packages in its set (for 81 total item stacks).

The §3Unpackager§r is a machine that extracts ingredient items from complete sets of Recipe Packages made in a Packager, ejecting the items into an adjacent inventory. It will only extract the items if §eall packages in a set are present§r.

When both a Packager and Unpackager are connected to an ME Network and have the same recipe, the resulting item will appear as craftable in your §aTerminal§r.

Unlike §aRF power§r, which is safe to transport in any §6conduit§r, §aEU power §r§erequires caution§r. The key is to always §amatch or exceed§r the §eVoltage §rand §eAmperage§r of your power source with your §6cables§r and machines.

§o§4§cNEVER §rhook up your CEF§r to a cable that has fewer §eAmps§r than your CEF or Battery Buffer§r generates. For example, you must use §64x cable§r for a 4x CEF§r, and §616x cable§r for a filled 16-slot Battery Buffer§r. Cables with insufficient amperage rating will §cburn and be destroyed§r. Similarly, your cable must match or exceed the §eVoltage§r of your machines, or they will §cburn and be destroyed§r.

§cNEVER§r connect a machine to excessive §eVoltage§r or it will §cvaporize§r. Touching a §6wire§r with connected §aEU power§r will §cinjure or kill you§r, so for your safety, §euse §6cables§e instead§r!

§3Battery Buffers§r are §bGregTech machines§r which can be filled with §aEU Batteries§r to provide §eone amp of power per battery they contain§r. These come in 1§r, 4§r, 9§r, and 16-slot§r variations.

The §3Large Microverse Projector§r is a more powerful projector required for sending Tier Seven through Tier Ten Micro Miners into microverses.

While some of the miners run on lower power, make a §6UV Energy Input§r so you don't have to replace it later or accidentally run something on insufficient power. Always check the voltage required on a recipe, as you will §close a miner§r if you can't supply enough power to complete the mission; ModMachines will continue to eat incoming power without making progress and breaking the structure voids the current craft.

When building the multiblock, be sure to place the §6Quantum Compressors§r to face the same direction as the controller block (this is the usual reason for the structure not forming).

The §3Lunar Mining Station§r is a large multiblock structure used for mining gases from the moon. It is an excellent (though not the only) source of §9Deuterium§r or §9Helium-3§r, depending on what kind of §6Rover§r you use.

Rovers only have a 10% chance to break while mining, so a stack of them will last quite a while.

Because this structure must be placed on the Moon, it is a good idea to use mechanisms like §aEnder Tanks§r or a §6Quantum Link Chamber§r for teleporting the fluids back to your base.

Make sure to keep it chunk-loaded!

§3Fluid Extractors§r are useful for melting things into liquids. For example, you can melt down ingots into molten metals, or §6Rubber Sheets§r into liquid §9Rubber§r.

When you have access to §6Steel§r, you can make molds and use §3Fluid Solidifiers§r to form various components more efficiently from fluids, like §6Gears§r.

Now that you have a §aFlux Capacitor§r to keep things charged, you might consider making yourself a §aFluxomagnet§r.

This relatively inexpensive bauble will suck nearby items into your inventory.

Fish Oil comes from, surprisingly, fish.

Aeügh.

A much more efficient version of the §3Empowerer§r.

This is a digital upgrade to the §3Crafting Core§r, allowing you to craft Empowerer recipes directly through §bPackagedAuto§r.

The §aMarked Pedestals§r can be placed freely within three blocks distance of the Crafting block, as long as they are on the same Y-level.

Useful to carry more stuff.

What more explanation are you expecting?
You'll need a Compressor for a variety of things, but probably most importantly is the ability to make plates from a single ingot.

An §3Autoclave§r is a machine that uses liquids (usually water) to polish stones, carve gems into lenses, infuse gems with special liquids, and crystallize various dusts.

You'll need an Autoclave for many recipes, but right now you want it to make §6Certus Quartz Crystals§r for §bApplied Energistics§r out of the §bGregTech§r §6Certus Quartz§r and its dust you get from mining and ore processing.

§aLumberaxes§f are tools that cut all connected blocks of the same kind (usually referred to as "§eveinmining§f") that require an axe. These are primarily intended to §echop down entire trees§f, but you can use them to veinmine other wooden blocks too.

§l§c§lKeep in mind that the veinmining feature doesn't get disabled when sneaking!§r

Please be careful to not veinmine your entire Storage Drawers network; this WILL end in tears.

Is it expensive? Yes. Is it worth it? Hell yes.

It doesn't start to shine until you get the good upgrades for it though, so maybe hold off for a while.

This terminal allows you to interact with fluid storage on your ME Network, like §aFluid Storage Disks§r.

Put fluids in or remove fluids via this terminal with any GUI-compatible container, by clicking on a fluid to fill it, or an empty space to drain into the network.

It's a micropart, so you need to place it on §6ME Cable§r (not a conduit).

§aStorage Drawer Controllers§r are the central hub of any good storage system. They can pull from any drawers they are connected to (via other drawers, or drawer trims) within a 12 block cubic radius. This leads to a potential 25x25x25 area to connect drawers, centered on the controller.

§aController Slaves§r do not extend the range, but rather act as another access point to that controller - allowing you to push/pull from any of the drawers within range of the local Drawer Controller.

Connecting an §6ME Storage Bus§f to a controller exposes all of the drawers to §bApplied Energistics§f. Particularly large networks can be laggy though, so keep your drawer networks a manageable size.

§bStorage Drawers§f provide a huge amount of storage for a single item type. Use them for things you have a lot of, such as stone, dirt and ores.

If the default appearances aren't your style, the §3Framing Table§f is useful for making custom drawers out of §6Framed Drawers§f and up to three additional items which define how the resulting drawer will look.
Great for automatically converting between Nuggets, Ingots, and Blocks of metals, or simply storing massive amounts of things.

When making circuits, you'll need either molten §9Tin§r, or molten §9Soldering Alloy§r§r§r in the §3Assembling Machine§r. Soldering Alloy is made in the §3Alloy Smelter§r with a 9:1 ratio of §6Tin Ingots§r to §6Antimony Dust§r. You then process it in a §3Fluid Extractor §rfor the usual 144mB of fluid per ingot.

The Assembling Machine will only consume half as much Soldering Alloy as it would have consumed molten Tin per craft (72mB vs 144mB), so it's very efficient to use this stuff.

Put your §3Centrifuge§r to work for the §6Antimony§r you'll need, which comes in tiny piles from processing §6Tetrahedrite Ore§r and §6Stibnite Ore§r.

Now that you have a §3Wiremill§r, you can turn one §6Copper Wire§r into four §6Fine Copper Wire§r. The recipes for §6Resistors§r, §6LV Motors§r and §6Vacuum Tubes§r all accept either type, so doing this extra processing step will make your §6Copper Ingots§r go §efour times further§r when making circuits.

You'll be making a lot more circuits from here on out, so its definitely worthwhile to save your copper!

betterquesting:10.name:8: The Fourth And Final Tier Three Circuits
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
With your new §6Fiber-Reinforced Epoxy Circuit Boards§r, §6Nano CPUs§r, and some standard components, you can make the final type of Tier Three Circuit: the §6Nanocircuit§r.

As the best form of Tier Three circuit, these should be automated and stockpiled. As with the Final Tier Two circuits, the §6System-on-Chip§r variant recipes won't be available for a while.

A small appetizer, before the §dOmnium§r main couse.

As the name suggests, this catalyst is formed from exotic non-elemental materials and alloys.

§6Capacitors§r are devices that store electrical energy, which is useful for circuits.

Not to be confused with §bEnderIO§r's capacitors§r, which store redstone flux.

Note: this quest accepts both LV and MV Brewery.

You can turn §6Plant Balls§r and other various §6sugary crops§r into §9Biomass§r with a §3Brewery§r. Biomass is the first step towards making Plastic in the form of §9Polyethylene§r.

The Brewery is a very very slow machine, but it requires almost no power. Building higher tier Breweries, or many LV ones, is necessary to brew enough Biomass for plastics.

§9Ethanol§r is alcohol, which you can first produce from distilling §9Biomass§r.

Boiling §6Sugar Cane§r in a §3Brewery§r is a great way to get Biomass, but you can also get it from other crops and saplings if you want.

Once you have a hefty starting stock of Ethanol, consider making and distilling §9Fermented Biomass§r in a §3Distillation Tower§r for extra chemicals.

You'll need §9Chlorine§r at this point. It is an important ingredient in many chemical processes. You can get it from electrolyzing §6Salt§r, among other sources.

Using a §3Mixer§r, you can create §9Salt Water§r and electrolyze that instead of plain Salt, which §edoubles the yield per Salt§r and provides you with useful §6Sodium Hydrodixe§r (NaOH).

§bEnderIO§r and §bThermal§r alloys are a bit more expensive than the normal wires, but they come with the huge advantage of being §elossless§r. Lossy cables like §6Tin§r and §6Copper§r will bleed out energy for every block they travel, but lossless ones do not.

The lossless cables for each tier are:

LV - Conductive Iron Cables
MV - Energetic Alloy Cables
HV - Vibrant Alloy Cables
EV - End Steel Cables
IV - Lumium Cables
LuV   - Signalum Cables
ZPMV - Enderium Cables
UV     - Draconium Cables
MaxV - Omnium Cables

MV and higher cables are made in an §3Assembling Machine§r. They're made with liquid §9Rubber§r and §6Wires§r, plus a reusable §6Programmed Circuit§r that tells it what thickness of wire to make.

You can use Wires, and for these materials they'll conduct just as well as if they were covered. But they'll §ckill you if you touch them while power is passing through§r, so... yeah. Your call.

Mix together these two crushed gems along with §9Resonant Ender§r to make §9Dew of the Void§r, the fluid that will power §bEnderIO§r interdimensional teleportation.

Please note that Dew of the Void goes great with Doritos.

§bEnderIO§r's equivalent of a §3Chemical Reactor§r, roughly speaking.

The only way to make several important liquids from EnderIO.

The §3Slice'N'Splice§r is a machine from §bEnderIO§r.

It is used for making monster-head-related items that are components for various things.

It needs to be supplied with an Axe and Shears, which are slowly damaged over time as items are crafted.

Not as common a component, but used in a number of critical machines.

Also useful as a machine cover for continuously moving items.

Robot Arms are components of several powerful machines, and are also useful as a machine cover for precise item movement.

One of the most expensive components, as it requires motors, pistons, and a circuit.

The §3Naquadah Reactor Mk1§r is a structure used to generate considerable amounts of RF power from decaying §6Enriched Naquadah§r or §6Naquadria§r into §6Lead§r.

§eKnown issue: Modular Machine energy output hatches cause a lot of lag by scanning a large region around it for the presence of a Draconic Evolution Energy Core to output into. This will hopefully be addressed in a future update.
Four §6Microprocessors§r combined with §6Titanium Plates§r and a few other standard components will make a §6Microprocessor Array§r.

Provides more augment slots to machines and dynamos.

Dynamos operate at §a1000% of base power and fuel burn rate§r.

Portable Tanks hold §a1250 buckets§r.

Machines operate at §a600% of base speed§r.
This compressor is needed for making §6Iridium Heavy Plating§r and §6Enderium Heavy Plating§r.
Upgrading to the §6Nanoprocessor Array§r requires some standard circuit components, but also some §6Lumium Wire§r and §6Tungstensteel Plates§r.

The first and most expensive Tier Six Circuit, needed for crafting the §3IV Assembling Machine§r.

Requires a bunch of standard circuit components, as well as multiple §6Lumium Wire§r and §6Tungstensteel Frames§r.
Nothing you haven't seen here: just combine some standard circuit components and §6Nanocircuits§r to make a §6Nanoprocessor§r.

With your §6Titanium§r-based machine hulls and §6Microprocessor Mainframes§r squared away, you can finally get on the path to making an Extreme Voltage §3Assembling Machine§r.

This tier of Assembling Machine unlocks §6Nanocircuits§r, as well as handling crafting recipes up to 2048 EU/t. It can also optionally overclock recipes up to 512 EU/t for improved speed at the cost of relatively more power.

Glowing!

This one takes a significant amount of time to cook, so make sure to have it going constantly.

Wires made from §6Lumium§r transmit IV power losslessly, and it forms the basis for §6LuV Machine Hulls§r.

What?!
§6STEAM DYNAMO§r is evolving!

Upgrade kits can be applied to Thermal Expansion Dynamos, machines, and even Portable Tanks. Machines and dynamos get additional augment slots.

When applied to a dynamo, it increases the §apower generation and fuel burn rate to 150%§r.

Increases the base capacity of Portable Tanks to §a200 buckets§r.

Allows machines operate at §a150% of base power per tick§r. The more power a machine can use, the faster it works.

With your §6Tungstensteel§r-based machine hulls and §6Nanoprocessor Mainframes§r squared away, you can finally get on the path to making an Insane Voltage §3Assembling Machine§r.

This tier of Assembling Machine unlocks §6Quantum Circuits§r, as well as handling crafting recipes up to 8192 EU/t. It can also optionally overclock recipes up to 2048 EU/t for improved speed at the cost of relatively more power.

With all of the components made, it's time to craft a §6Primitive Circuit§r.

This is where your §3Worktable§f setups will really shine! With the patterns encoded into a Worktable (well, really over §omany§r Worktables), you'll be able to §ebatch craft circuits quickly§f.

You'll be making a LOT§r of circuits, so take advantage of the improved crafting efficiency.

Now that you have an §3Assembly Line§r you can craft the §6Quantum Processor Mainframe§r, the first Tier Seven circuit.

These are required for crafting the Ludicrous Voltage (LuV) §3Assembling Machine§r.

This recipe requires some §6Quantum Stars§r, which are made in a §3Chemical Bath§r with a §6Nether Star§r and §9Radon§r. It also needs some §6HSS-G Frames§r and significant quantities of §6SMD Components§r.

The §3HV Assembling Machine§r unlocks §6Microcircuits§r, as well as handling crafting recipes up to 512 EU/t.

It can also optionally overclock recipes up to 128 EU/t, gaining additional speed for relatively more power.

With your §6Iridium§r-based machine hulls and §6Crystal Processor Mainframes§r squared away, you can finally get on the path to making a ZPM §3Assembling Machine§r.

This tier of Assembling Machine unlocks §6Wetware Circuits§r, as well as handling crafting recipes up to 131072 EU/t. It can also optionally overclock recipes up to 32768 EU/t for improved speed at the cost of relatively more power.
With §6Draconium§r, §6Enderium§r, and some §6HPICs§r, you can assemble a §6Crystal Processor Array§r.

The §6Crystal Processor Mainframe§r is the first Tier Eight circuit.

Along with things you already know how to make, this needs §6HSS-E Frames§r.

These are required for crafting the §3ZPM Assembling Machine§r. As usual, these are extremely expensive: invest in the next theme of circuits instead of trying to mass-produce these.

§6ZPM Machine Hulls§r are made with §6Iridium Plates§r, but you'll notice they also need §9Polytetrafluoroethylene§r (more commonly known as Teflon™), a special plastic which will be required for all machine hulls going forward.

ZPM stands for Zero Point Module.

This is the last tier of machine that's sensible to produce before you reach the §dCreative Portable Tank§r. Multiblock hatches are a different matter- feel free to upgrade your §3EBF§rs to Ultimate Voltage, if you can handle the power drain. There's no usable tier above that, though.

§9Sterilized Growth Medium§r is needed for §6Wetware Circuits§r.

You'll need to mix §6Mincemeat§r, §6Sugar§r, and §6Tiny piles of Salt§r with water in a mixer to make §9Raw Growth Medium§r, then use a §3Fluid Heater§r to sterilize it.

Mincemeat comes from pulverizing any kind of animal meat. A §aPowered Spawner§r might be useful for this endeavor.

These two dusts will be used in a variety of upcoming chemical reactions.

§6Phosphor§r can be obtained by processing §6Phosphor Ore§r into dust and electrolyzing several times. This ore is found in §6Apatite§r veins.

§6Sulfur§r can be electrolyzed easily from §6Sphalerite§r (which also provides §6Gallium§r), §6Cinnabar§r, and §6Pyrite§r. Alternately, Sulfur can be acquired through §bDeep Mob Learning§r- look into that quest line if you haven't already.

The §3Extruder§r is an alternative way to form shapes from metal. §aExtruder Shapes§r are used for telling an Extruder which shape to make.

Extruders are the only way to make certain things, like §6Large Pipes§r. Extruders use ingots, but are as efficient for making §6Gears§r as melting and solidifying.

You can also use Extruders to make things from other machines like plates and wires, but they are less efficient than using the dedicated machines for these purposes.

Overclocking aside, as you continue to progress in §5Omnifactory§f, materials made in the §3Electric Blast Furnace§f will take longer to complete. §eMore advanced coils do not give speed bonuses§f, only allowing for the furnace to §eget hot enough to process more advanced materials§f.

Consequently, you'll need to continually expand your smelting and power generation infrastructure.

You don't have to get all four of these Electric Blast Furnaces completed and running just yet, but be prepared to make many of them over the course of the pack.

The §3Soul Binder§r is an §bEnderIO§r machine which uses §aSoul Vials§r and Experience to enhance specific items.

It may be prudent to store §9Liquid XP§r in an adjacent §3Obelisk§r, which the Soul Binder can draw from directly, or you can insert it using other standard means of fluid routing.
Carry even more stuff.
Carry §oeven more§r stuff.

betterquesting:10.name:8: I Dont Need No Stinkin' Tower
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Note: this quest accepts both LV and MV Distillery.

If you don't feel up to making a §3Distillation Tower§r just yet, you can get §9Ethanol§r via a single block §3Distillery§r, a machine that gets one fluid and §cvoids the rest§r (in this case, Water). This defers the tower for a little while longer.

However, the Distillation Tower is mandatory for advanced chemistry, as most things have more than one important output: §9Fermented Biomass§r, §9Charcoal Byproducts§r from your §3Pyrolyse Oven§r, and the entire line of petrochemicals from §9Oil§r, to name a few.

Can't avoid it forever!

A good way to find a specific ore you're missing is the §6Scanner Module: Block§r for your Scanner. §6Sneak-right click§f a piece of ore you want to search for with a Module in your hand, then §6sneak-right click§f the §aScanner§f, put the module inside, and go wander around scanning. 

The range is significantly longer than it is when using the modules which detect all ores, and you even have room for a second §6Range Module§f if you've got an §6Ender Pearl§f to craft one.

You can combo this with ores bought from §dOmnicoins§f to act as a "sample" to easily find a full vein with the Block Module.

§aMolds§r are used in a §3Fluid Solidifier§r or §3Alloy Smelter§r to form materials into specific shapes. These are not consumed or damaged during crafting, so you can leave them in a machine to dedicate it to that shape.

The Fluid Solidifier tends to be the more efficient option: for example, you can use §e8 ingots§r to make one §6Gear§r in an Alloy Smelter, but with a Fluid Extractor and Solidifier you can accomplish the same result with §e4 ingots§r.

Be careful not to accidentally make §aExtruder Shapes§r. Those are for a machine you will get access to later. The two molds in this quest are ones you will find useful right away.

If you don't like the idea of mining out Oilsands veins, you can build an §3Oil Drilling Rig§r.

You'll need to provide it with power, §9Drilling Fluid§r, and a steady supply of §6Pipes§r. The Pipes only have a 1% chance to have one be used up per bucket of §9Oil§r drilled.

Place the §3Vertical Digger§r over an ore vein, feed it RF, and it will mine up the entire vein for you.

For drills, you will need a §6GregTech Drill§r (any LV drill will work), a §6Fluxbore§r (Reinforced tier is required) and an §6Actually Additions Drill§r (any color is fine, but take out any augments you wish to keep).

The GregTech Drill will not be consumed, but everything else will be.

Up to three §aPhantom Boosters§r can be placed atop the §3Vertical Digger§r to increase its area of effect.

These are also useful for extending the range of other "Phantom" machines and devices from §bActually Additions§r.

Being able to fly is pretty sick. Its also pretty expensive.

Its probably a bit premature to consider a §6jetpack§r at this point, but if you really want to craft this bad boy, I won't stop you.

There's also a quest chain for §bEnderIO§r Jetpacks (starting with the §6Conductive Iron Jetpack§r). Eventually you'll need to make both, but not for a long time, so feel free to ignore at least one of these quest chains unless you really really like flying.
Better flying.

Even better flying.

You're not getting up to Resonant for a long time, just FYI.
§6Rich Phyto-Gro§r can be further enhanced by infusing it with Redstone Flux in the §3Energetic Infuser§r.

Now that you have a §3Wiremill§f and a §3Compressor§f, you can consider starting to do §eBounties§f. The §6Bounty Board§f has a global inventory containing quests to turn in specific items in exchange for §dOmnicoins§f. These quests have a fairly short duration, so make sure to §estockpile the items§f that come up on them or else they'll §cexpire before you can complete them§f.

With renewable §dOmnicoins§f, you should feel free to spend the ones you have on whatever you need. §aSpend your coins!

This is an augment that will work in all §3dynamos§f. It increases the efficiency of the fuel being used inside the dynamo, increasing the power it generates. However, the rate of power generation remains the same, the fuel simply lasts longer. So while §6Fuel Catalyzers§f decrease the amount you'll need to go mining for §6Coal§f, they won't boost your production of RF per second.

Each Fuel Catalyzer increases fuel efficiency by §a15%§f, additively (so two will make fuel last §a30% longer§f, three is §a45% longer§f, etc).

The §aAuxiliary Transmission Coil §ris an augment that will work in all types of dynamos. It will consume fuel faster to produce a correspondingly higher RF per tick.

Each augment increases both base power production and fuel consumption by 100%, additively (so the second is 200%, third is 300%, etc).

Consider the tradeoffs however, as you could just make another dynamo, and you miss out on §aFuel Catalyzer§r augments that make fuels burn longer for more total RF generated. The Auxiliary Transmission Coil will put additional stress your fuel production infrastructure.

If that's an acceptable tradeoff, then Auxiliary Transmission Coils are a cheap and effective way to boost your power production.

Wires made from §6Naquadah§r are ZPM tier.

§6Naquadah Cables§r are needed, among other things, for §6ZPM Machine Hulls§r.

How much do you think these solar panels weigh? 

These are quite expensive and two of them are required for each Tier Ten Micro Miner.

§6Neutronium Solar Panels§r generate an enormous amount of RF power in sunlight, so once you get your tank it's also a good choice for compact power generation.

Protip: it's always daytime in space.

As you continue to progress, crafting times for more advanced §3Electric Blast Furnace§r recipes will continue to increase. More advanced coils do not give speed bonuses, they just increase the operating temperature so you can smelt more advanced materials.

To compensate, you'll need to get your infrastructure for smelting, as well as for power generation, up to snuff.

You don't need to get all eight of these completed and running just yet, but plan to at some point in the future. Instead of upgrading existing EBFs, have them passively automating a stock of materials and build new EBFs with higher specifications for new materials.

betterquesting:10.name:8: High Speed Steel Type E Ingot
High Speed Steel Type G Ingots
High Speed Steel Type S Ingots

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
No hypothetical aliens were harmed in the harvesting of this item.

Probably.

Melting the heart of a universe provides a rather useful liquid: §dMolten Creative Portable Tank§r.

You are become Death, destroyer of Universes.

Might probably be obvious, but this miner gathers §6Heart of a Universe§r.

Kind of redundant, really.

This plating is used exclusively for the Tier Ten Micro Miner. You need some serious protection from forces when harvesting a whole microverse.

§6Neutronium§r is a hyper-dense material normally found in the hearts of neutron stars: the collapsed cores of stars between ten and thirty times the size of the sun.

Fun fact: a single neutronium block is approximately 2884 million metric tons and somewhere around 600000K, yet you're somehow capable of holding one with your bare hands. Don't think about it too much.

Neutronium is made from fusing molten §9Naquadria§r, a super-enriched form of §6Naquadah§r, with molten §9Americium§r. These bad boys require a LOT of time to fuse.

Parallelizing fluid crafting is tricky business (and Mark 3 reactors are expensive), but several could be used to speed up the processing. Try to minimize your reactor's downtime and be very careful about supplying your reactors with stable power.

After getting §6Chaotic Fusion Injectors§r, you might consider using Tier Nine Micro Miners to supplement the fusion, as it is net-positive for Neutronium. These miners are expensive though, so it's up to you.
